	<text>
		<body>
			<p><pb n="1" facs="EHRI-ET-ZIH3010317_01.jpg"/></p>
			<p><persName ref="#ehri_et_bialoszer_niusia">Białoszer Niusia</persName>, born on the <date when="1923-05-30">30th of May, 1923</date> in
					<placeName ref="http://www.geonames.org/756135/warsaw.html">Warsaw</placeName>. <term
					ref="https://portal.ehri-project.eu/keywords/ehri_terms-822" type="subject">Daughter</term> of <persName
					ref="#ehri_et_bialoszer_josel">Josel</persName> and <persName ref="#ehri_et_bialoszer_dwora">Dwora</persName>, <term
					ref="https://portal.ehri-project.eu/keywords/ehri_terms-822" type="subject">mother</term> née <persName
					ref="#ehri_et_bialoszer_dwora">Bieniakońska</persName>.</p>
			<p>Education: secondary school (matura). <term ref="https://portal.ehri-project.eu/keywords/ehri_terms-819" type="subject">Family</term>:
				not married. Profession: before the <term ref="https://portal.ehri-project.eu/keywords/ehri_terms-1080" type="subject">war</term> – at
				school, during the <term ref="https://portal.ehri-project.eu/keywords/ehri_terms-1080" type="subject">war</term> and at present –
				office employee.</p>
			<p>During the <term ref="https://portal.ehri-project.eu/keywords/ehri_terms-1080" type="subject">war</term> more or less the whole <term
					ref="https://portal.ehri-project.eu/keywords/ehri_terms-819" type="subject">family</term>
				<term ref="https://portal.ehri-project.eu/keywords/ehri_terms-745" type="subject">perished</term>. I survived alone with my <term
					ref="https://portal.ehri-project.eu/keywords/ehri_terms-822" type="subject">mother</term>.</p>
			<p>When the <term ref="https://portal.ehri-project.eu/keywords/ehri_terms-1080" type="subject">war</term> broke out, I was living in
					<placeName ref="http://www.geonames.org/593116/vilnius.html">Vilnius</placeName> with my <term
					ref="https://portal.ehri-project.eu/keywords/ehri_terms-822" type="subject">mother</term>. We lived at <placeName
					ref="http://www.geonames.org/593116/vilnius.html">Vilner Street number 4</placeName>.</p>
			<p>On the <date when="1941-06-21">21st of June, 1941</date> the <term ref="https://portal.ehri-project.eu/keywords/ehri_terms-1080"
					type="subject">war</term> between <term ref="https://portal.ehri-project.eu/keywords/ehri_terms-1159" type="subject"
					>Germany</term> and the <placeName ref="http://www.geonames.org/8354411/union-of-soviet-socialist-republics.html">Soviet
					Union</placeName> broke out. When the <term ref="https://portal.ehri-project.eu/keywords/ehri_terms-1080" type="subject"
					>war</term> broke out, I and my <term ref="https://portal.ehri-project.eu/keywords/ehri_terms-819" type="subject">family</term>
				were living in <placeName ref="http://www.geonames.org/593116/vilnius.html">Vilnius</placeName>, at <placeName
					ref="http://www.geonames.org/593116/vilnius.html">Vilner Street number 4</placeName>.</p>
			<p>The town was bombarded by <term ref="https://portal.ehri-project.eu/keywords/ehri_terms-1159" type="subject">German</term> planes for
				two days.</p>
			<p>On the <date when="1941-06-23">23rd of June, 1941</date> the <orgName ref="https://portal.ehri-project.eu/authorities/ehri_cb-438"
					>German army</orgName> marched into <placeName ref="http://www.geonames.org/593116/vilnius.html">Vilnius</placeName>. The city has
				fallen without a fight.</p>
			<p>There were 70 000 Jews in <placeName ref="http://www.geonames.org/593116/vilnius.html">Vilnius</placeName>. A considerable part of
				young Jewish people succeeded to <term ref="https://portal.ehri-project.eu/keywords/ehri_terms-204" type="subject">escape</term> to
				the <placeName ref="http://www.geonames.org/8354411/union-of-soviet-socialist-republics.html">Soviet Union</placeName>. But many of
				them were <term ref="https://portal.ehri-project.eu/keywords/ehri_terms-532" type="subject">killed</term> on their way. Just after the
				city was taken by the <term ref="https://portal.ehri-project.eu/keywords/ehri_terms-1159" type="subject">Germans</term>, the city
				municipality <term ref="https://portal.ehri-project.eu/keywords/ehri_terms-585" type="subject">confiscated</term> all Jewish
				businesses and real estate.</p>
			<p>The Jews were forced to start to sell away their possessions in order to buy <term
					ref="https://portal.ehri-project.eu/keywords/ehri_terms-832" type="subject">food</term>.</p>
			<p><term ref="#ehri_et_nationalities_lithuanians">Lithuanians</term> hang out posters in cinemas, cafés and shops: <q><term
						ref="https://portal.ehri-project.eu/keywords/ehri_terms-339" type="subject">Entry for Jews is forbidden</term>.</q></p>
			<p><term ref="https://portal.ehri-project.eu/keywords/ehri_terms-1159" type="subject">German</term><term
					ref="https://portal.ehri-project.eu/keywords/ehri_terms-1097" type="subject">soldiers</term>, as well as <term
					ref="#ehri_et_nationalities_lithuanians">Lithuanian</term><term ref="https://portal.ehri-project.eu/keywords/ehri_terms-1119"
					type="subject">policemen</term>, went to Jewish homes, beat Jews and took away their valuables.</p>
			<p>The <orgName ref="https://portal.ehri-project.eu/authorities/ehri_cb-350">Gestapo</orgName> and the <orgName
					ref="https://portal.ehri-project.eu/authorities/ehri_cb-429">SS</orgName> destroyed all the <term
					ref="https://portal.ehri-project.eu/keywords/ehri_terms-758" type="subject">synagogues</term>, burned and stamped on Torah scrolls
				and religious books.</p>
			<p>One day three <term ref="https://portal.ehri-project.eu/keywords/ehri_terms-1159" type="subject">German</term>
				<term ref="https://portal.ehri-project.eu/keywords/ehri_terms-1097" type="subject">soldiers</term> and two <term
					ref="#ehri_et_nationalities_lithuanians">Lithuanian</term></p>
			<p><pb n="2" facs="EHRI-ET-ZIH3010317_02.jpg"/></p>
			<p><term ref="https://portal.ehri-project.eu/keywords/ehri_terms-1119" type="subject">policemen</term> with guns in their hands came to
				our home. They ordered us to remain sitting where we were. They menaced us that they would <term
					ref="https://portal.ehri-project.eu/keywords/ehri_terms-532" type="subject">shoot</term> anyone who would make a move. One of the
					<term ref="#ehri_et_nationalities_lithuanians">Lithuanians</term> stayed to guard us, and others searched through the whole
				apartment. They left after taking all the valuables.</p>
			<p>The <term ref="https://portal.ehri-project.eu/keywords/ehri_terms-1159" type="subject">German</term> authorities forced the Jews to pay
				a contribution of 1 000 000 roubles. The order was made known through posters on the walls of buildings.</p>
			<p>In order to raise the sum, Jews gave away their last money and jewelry. Many even gave away their wedding rings. The contribution was
				raised.</p>
			<p>At the same time, a hundred Jewish <term ref="https://portal.ehri-project.eu/keywords/ehri_terms-663" type="subject">hostages</term>
				were <term ref="https://portal.ehri-project.eu/keywords/ehri_terms-598" type="subject">arrested</term>. The <orgName
					ref="https://portal.ehri-project.eu/authorities/ehri_cb-350">Gestapo</orgName> and the <orgName
					ref="https://portal.ehri-project.eu/authorities/ehri_cb-429">SS</orgName>
				<term ref="https://portal.ehri-project.eu/keywords/ehri_terms-826" type="subject">men</term> came to the <term
					ref="https://portal.ehri-project.eu/keywords/ehri_terms-872" type="subject">Jewish community</term> office and <term
					ref="https://portal.ehri-project.eu/keywords/ehri_terms-598" type="subject">arrested</term> all the employees. Among them were
					<persName ref="#ehri_et_wygodzki_jakub">Jakub Wygodzki</persName> (the chairman of the <term
					ref="https://portal.ehri-project.eu/keywords/ehri_terms-872" type="subject">community</term>), <persName
					ref="#ehri_et_trotzki_saul">Saul Trocki</persName>, <persName ref="#ehri_et_kruk_e">Kruk</persName>, <persName
					ref="#ehri_et_langbard">Langbard</persName> and the <term ref="https://portal.ehri-project.eu/keywords/ehri_terms-899"
					type="subject">lawyer</term>
				<persName ref="#ehri_et_katsenelson">Katsenelson</persName>.</p>
			<p>Other <term ref="https://portal.ehri-project.eu/keywords/ehri_terms-663" type="subject">hostages</term> were <term
					ref="https://portal.ehri-project.eu/keywords/ehri_terms-735" type="subject">rabbis</term> and Jewish intelligentsia. The <orgName
					ref="https://portal.ehri-project.eu/authorities/ehri_cb-429">SS</orgName>
				<term ref="https://portal.ehri-project.eu/keywords/ehri_terms-598" type="subject">arrested</term> them in their own homes. Engineer
					<persName ref="#ehri_et_vigushin">Vigushin</persName> and <term ref="https://portal.ehri-project.eu/keywords/ehri_terms-735"
					type="subject">rabbi</term>
				<persName ref="#ehri_et_fried">Frid</persName> were among them.</p>
			<p>After a few days the Gebietskommissar <persName ref="https://portal.ehri-project.eu/authorities/ehri_pers-000894">Hingst</persName>
				issued an <term ref="https://portal.ehri-project.eu/keywords/ehri_terms-339" type="subject">order</term> that was posted on the walls
				of buildings: <q>Jews must <term ref="https://portal.ehri-project.eu/keywords/ehri_terms-339" type="subject">give away all of their
						jewelry, gold and silver</term>.</q> And a second <term ref="https://portal.ehri-project.eu/keywords/ehri_terms-339"
					type="subject">order</term>: <q>Jews are <term ref="https://portal.ehri-project.eu/keywords/ehri_terms-339" type="subject"
						>forbidden to walk on the sidewalks and to travel by car, tram or train</term>. Jews <term
						ref="https://portal.ehri-project.eu/keywords/ehri_terms-339" type="subject">cannot set foot in the main streets of the
						city</term>, such as <placeName ref="http://www.geonames.org/593116/vilnius.html">Zawalna</placeName>, <placeName
						ref="http://www.geonames.org/593116/vilnius.html">Mickiewicza</placeName>, <placeName
						ref="http://www.geonames.org/593116/vilnius.html">Trocka</placeName>, <placeName
						ref="http://www.geonames.org/593116/vilnius.html">Pohulanka</placeName>, <placeName
						ref="http://www.geonames.org/593116/vilnius.html">Zakretowa</placeName>, <placeName
						ref="http://www.geonames.org/593116/vilnius.html">Wielka</placeName>.</q> At the same time the <term
					ref="https://portal.ehri-project.eu/keywords/ehri_terms-1159" type="subject">German</term> authorities issued the following <term
					ref="https://portal.ehri-project.eu/keywords/ehri_terms-339" type="subject">order</term> in the form of a poster: <q>All Jews from
					three years old must carry <term ref="https://portal.ehri-project.eu/keywords/ehri_terms-338" type="subject">patches</term> on the
					left side of breast and back. The <term ref="https://portal.ehri-project.eu/keywords/ehri_terms-338" type="subject">patches</term>
					must be fabricated from white <term ref="https://portal.ehri-project.eu/keywords/ehri_terms-836" type="subject">cloth</term>, 10
					centimetres wide with an embroidered <term ref="https://portal.ehri-project.eu/keywords/ehri_terms-338" type="subject">yellow
						circle and a letter J in the centre</term>.</q></p>
			<p><pb n="3" facs="EHRI-ET-ZIH3010317_03.jpg"/></p>
			<p>This <term ref="https://portal.ehri-project.eu/keywords/ehri_terms-338" type="subject">patch</term> was changed into another, in the
				form of a <term ref="https://portal.ehri-project.eu/keywords/ehri_terms-338" type="subject">yellow star of David</term> on the breast
				and on the back. The <term ref="https://portal.ehri-project.eu/keywords/ehri_terms-338" type="subject">patch</term> remained like that
				until the end.</p>
			<p>At that time <term ref="https://portal.ehri-project.eu/keywords/ehri_terms-550" type="subject">roundups</term> of Jewish <term
					ref="https://portal.ehri-project.eu/keywords/ehri_terms-826" type="subject">men</term> started. <term
					ref="https://portal.ehri-project.eu/keywords/ehri_terms-1159" type="subject">German</term>
				<orgName ref="https://portal.ehri-project.eu/authorities/ehri_cb-429">SS</orgName> and <term ref="#ehri_et_nationalities_lithuanians"
					>Lithuanian</term>
				<term ref="https://portal.ehri-project.eu/keywords/ehri_terms-1119" type="subject">police</term> would <term
					ref="https://portal.ehri-project.eu/keywords/ehri_terms-550" type="subject">round up</term> Jewish <term
					ref="https://portal.ehri-project.eu/keywords/ehri_terms-826" type="subject">men</term> on the streets or go into Jewish homes and
				take away both old and young without any difference. They would even drag out the <term
					ref="https://portal.ehri-project.eu/keywords/ehri_terms-292" type="subject">sick</term> from their beds. By such means the
					<orgName ref="https://portal.ehri-project.eu/authorities/ehri_cb-429">SS</orgName> would <term
					ref="https://portal.ehri-project.eu/keywords/ehri_terms-550" type="subject">round up</term> a few hundred Jews every day. It was
				supposed to be for <term ref="https://portal.ehri-project.eu/keywords/ehri_terms-556" type="subject">work</term>. But instead of <term
					ref="https://portal.ehri-project.eu/keywords/ehri_terms-556" type="subject">work</term>, the <orgName
					ref="https://portal.ehri-project.eu/authorities/ehri_cb-429">SS</orgName> would bring the Jewish <term
					ref="https://portal.ehri-project.eu/keywords/ehri_terms-826" type="subject">men</term> to the <placeName ref="#ehri_et_lukiszki"
					>Łukiszki</placeName>
				<term ref="https://portal.ehri-project.eu/keywords/ehri_terms-669" type="subject">prison</term> and from there to a forest 12
				kilometers from <placeName ref="http://www.geonames.org/593116/vilnius.html">Vilnius</placeName>. The forest is called <q><placeName
						ref="http://www.geonames.org/596134/paneriai.html">Ponar</placeName></q>. In the beginning we thought that <q><placeName
						ref="http://www.geonames.org/596134/paneriai.html">Ponar</placeName></q> was a <term
					ref="https://portal.ehri-project.eu/keywords/ehri_terms-508" type="subject">work camp</term>. Gradually we became aware that it
				was a place of <term ref="https://portal.ehri-project.eu/keywords/ehri_terms-541" type="subject">executions</term> and that the
					<orgName ref="https://portal.ehri-project.eu/authorities/ehri_cb-429">SS</orgName> tortured and <term
					ref="https://portal.ehri-project.eu/keywords/ehri_terms-532" type="subject">shot</term> about 10 000 of our <term
					ref="https://portal.ehri-project.eu/keywords/ehri_terms-826" type="subject">men</term> there.</p>
			<p>In <date when="1941-08">August 1941</date> rumours about closing the Jews in a <term
					ref="https://portal.ehri-project.eu/keywords/ehri_terms-545" type="subject">ghetto</term> started to spread.</p>
			<p>The <term ref="https://portal.ehri-project.eu/keywords/ehri_terms-1159" type="subject">German</term> Gebietskommissar <persName
					ref="https://portal.ehri-project.eu/authorities/ehri_pers-000894">Hingst</persName> and the <term
					ref="#ehri_et_nationalities_lithuanians">Lithuanian</term> mayor <persName ref="#ehri_et_burokas">Burokas</persName> called a
				meeting with some of their employees and worked out the plan of the <term ref="https://portal.ehri-project.eu/keywords/ehri_terms-545"
					type="subject">ghetto</term>.</p>
			<p>On Saturday, the <date when="1941-08-31">31st of August 1941</date>, the <term
					ref="https://portal.ehri-project.eu/keywords/ehri_terms-1159" type="subject">German</term> authorities hung out the following
				posters: <q>On the corner of <placeName ref="http://www.geonames.org/593116/vilnius.html">Breyte</placeName> and <placeName
						ref="http://www.geonames.org/593116/vilnius.html">Glezer streets</placeName>, the Jews have <term
						ref="https://portal.ehri-project.eu/keywords/ehri_terms-532" type="subject">murdered</term> two <term
						ref="https://portal.ehri-project.eu/keywords/ehri_terms-1159" type="subject">German</term>
					<term ref="https://portal.ehri-project.eu/keywords/ehri_terms-1097" type="subject">soldiers</term> in a terrible way. We have to
					take revenge for their blood.</q></p>
			<p>On Sunday, the <date when="1941-09-01">1st of September 1941</date>, at midnight the <term ref="#ehri_et_nationalities_lithuanians"
					>Lithuanian</term>
				<orgName ref="https://portal.ehri-project.eu/authorities/ehri_cb-429">SS</orgName> encircled the streets that were largely inhabited
				by Jews: <placeName ref="http://www.geonames.org/593116/vilnius.html">Żydowska</placeName>, <placeName
					ref="http://www.geonames.org/593116/vilnius.html">Niemiecka</placeName>, <placeName
					ref="http://www.geonames.org/593116/vilnius.html">Dziśnieńska</placeName>, <placeName
					ref="http://www.geonames.org/593116/vilnius.html">Jatkowa</placeName> and a part of <placeName
					ref="http://www.geonames.org/593116/vilnius.html">Wielka</placeName>.</p>
			<p><pb n="4" facs="EHRI-ET-ZIH3010317_04.jpg"/></p>
			<p><term ref="#ehri_et_nationalities_lithuanians">Lithuanian</term><term ref="https://portal.ehri-project.eu/keywords/ehri_terms-1097"
					type="subject">soldiers</term> entered the Jewish homes and dragged away even the old and the <term
					ref="https://portal.ehri-project.eu/keywords/ehri_terms-824" type="subject">children</term> naked from their beds, not giving them
				any time to put some <term ref="https://portal.ehri-project.eu/keywords/ehri_terms-836" type="subject">clothes</term> on. The <term
					ref="https://portal.ehri-project.eu/keywords/ehri_terms-825" type="subject">women</term> wept and the <term
					ref="https://portal.ehri-project.eu/keywords/ehri_terms-824" type="subject">children</term> cried out for their <term
					ref="https://portal.ehri-project.eu/keywords/ehri_terms-822" type="subject">mothers</term>.</p>
			<p>The <term ref="#ehri_et_nationalities_lithuanians">Lithuanians</term> drove everyone out in the street with no mercy. It was completely
				dark outside. The <term ref="https://portal.ehri-project.eu/keywords/ehri_terms-826" type="subject">men</term> lost their <term
					ref="https://portal.ehri-project.eu/keywords/ehri_terms-822" type="subject">wives</term> in the crowd and the <term
					ref="https://portal.ehri-project.eu/keywords/ehri_terms-825" type="subject">women</term> – their <term
					ref="https://portal.ehri-project.eu/keywords/ehri_terms-824" type="subject">children</term>. No one could orient themselves where
				the others were.</p>
			<p>During this provocation 4000 Jews were <term ref="https://portal.ehri-project.eu/keywords/ehri_terms-550" type="subject">rounded
					up</term>.</p>
			<p>The <term ref="#ehri_et_nationalities_lithuanians">Lithuanian</term>
				<orgName ref="https://portal.ehri-project.eu/authorities/ehri_cb-429">SS</orgName> encircled them with a strong guard and marched them
				to the <placeName ref="#ehri_et_lukiszki">Łukiszki</placeName>
				<term ref="https://portal.ehri-project.eu/keywords/ehri_terms-669" type="subject">prison</term>.</p>
			<p>From there the <term ref="#ehri_et_nationalities_lithuanians">Lithuanians</term> took them by trucks to <placeName
					ref="http://www.geonames.org/596134/paneriai.html">Ponar</placeName>.</p>
